  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Citizens participation in local governance, gender equity and social inclusion, for economic develop</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mobilization and Networking-Creating a reliable network of NGOs, FBOs, CBOs, Traditional leaders, Community Protection Teams sensitize and educate
Lobbying and engagement with various duty bearers by right holder groups to try to change the status quo using forums
Stakeholders&#x2019; sensitisation and education meetings-Organise seminars and training (in cooperation with Network of NGOs, FBOs, CBOs, identified change agents among the chiefs) in the communities and at the district level on law and policy
 Media, Radio and TV education and campaign-Organize community radio programs, to sensitize the public on issues related to Citizens participation in local governance, gender equity and social inclusion and on law and policies</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To strengthen the cultural and political transformation that has already begun in the selected communities to give children and women voices at local and district levels. Further to increase women&#x2019;s participation at district political level as well as demand accountability for their share in national policies, eg planting for food and jobs, one district, one factory.</narrative>
  </description>
